  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed and discussed in narrative but UQ artifacts are not linked to all validation results. Full 13-factor assessment covering software quality, code verification, discretization error, test conditions, output comparison, relevance of QoI, relevance of validation activities, numerical solver error, use error, model form, model inputs, test samples, and equivalency of input parameters.",
